      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm working on this legal tech project in brussels. need a python function to pull out mandatory regulatory requirements from these text blocks. i've got some test cases i'm using to check if the extraction is accurate enough for our compliance standards. can u write a function that passes these?\n\ntext_block = \"Under Article 5, the controller shall implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure a level of security appropriate to the risk. Data subjects must be informed of any breach clearly and without undue delay.\"\n\ndef test_extraction():\n    requirements = extract_requirements(text_block)\n    expected = [\"implement appropriate technical and organizational measures\", \"be informed of any breach\"]\n    assert all(req in requirements for req in expected), f\"Failed! Got: {requirements}\"\n    print(\"Tests passed!\")\n\nextract_requirements(text_block)",
